  <refnamediv>
    <refname>isfilterseparable</refname>
    <refpurpose>Checks whether the given filter/kernel is separable or not.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   bool check = isfilterseparable("filter",kernel)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>filter:</term>
      <listitem><para> filter/kernel values</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>check :</term>
      <listitem><para> Boolean variable which tells whether the kernel is separable(1) or not(0).</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
The function finds the rank of the kernel. If it is 1, then the function returns a boolean value 1 signifying that the filter is separable;
else it returns boolean value 0 signifying it is not separable.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
//Sobel filter
sobel = [-1 0 1; -2 0 2; -1 0 1];
//Executing function
isfilterseparable("filter",sobel)

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

